<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Pharaohedge</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Woods Person</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jul 09, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 45</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">From: Biloxi<br></FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-07-19 15:24&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">I want to take up smithing. After getting my human druid up to level 8, buying all the level 9 spells in anticipation, getting frustrated as hell with not getting any exp for some damn reason, I decided to switch to a High Elf Wizard. This seemed like the optimum smithing class- High INT for trade skill AND class, teleport which always helps most any trade, and cultural smithing of Mithril. God what a pain it was. I didn't make one level, I'm back to my human druid. Why? High WIS for trade skill AND class, teleporting which always helps most any trade, cutural smithing for humans, plus added strength of humans plus strength buffing for added help with smithing. Honestly, I was obsessing over this for a few days. Finally I just said screw it, one class is as good as another and my druid is already level 8, and times a wasting as I pay $10 a month so pick one. (One class as good as another... lol the lies we tell ourselves.) What do you all think? Do I have these pros and cons right? Should I just make an alt to trade all my stuff off to for smithing? What are your personal ideas of the best smithing class?</FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#f7f5e6"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=954"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Pharaohedge"></a>
