<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Fwin Peaks</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Chip off the Ol Treant</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jun 12, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 30</FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-07-19 16:20&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">My recommendation?  Play what is fun for you.  It all evens out in the long run - with items that enhance certain stats, buffs, potions, etc.  I honestly think people obsess over having the right 'mix' of stats, when in reality there's a 'probability generator' churning in the background that is random for skill increases anyway.  I'm an ugly, weak, low-int, but high-wis halfling and I've managed to master all tradeskills and general skills except for jewelcraft and fletching.<BR><BR>The only sure-fire way to master tradeskills quickly is to have a higher level char PL you, or if you have loads of plat to dump into it.<BR><BR>Starting a character for tradeskills is only relevant if you want to master jewelcraft.  Too durned expensive otherwise.  <BR><BR>If you're targetting smithing, then what does it matter if stats enable you to trivial banded armor in 450 tries as opposed to 500 tries - especially if you're not going to enjoy your character?<BR><BR>Don't mean to sound preachy -- it's just that Verant added tradeskills later in development.  Stats are enhancements to success, but characters really weren't designed to be 'tradeskill master-craftsmen'.<BR><BR>
<BR>_________________<BR>Fwin Peaks<BR>Hairy Front and Leatherfoot Breeder<BR>49<BR>Druzzil Ro</FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=15"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Fwin Peaks"></a>
