<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">You don't have to go with just one tradeskill (except for choosing which one you'll carry on over 200 skill). Many smiths decide to take up tailoring as well (or vice versa) as an efficient use/application of boning/studs in the leather armour line.<BR><BR>Druids, once they begin foraging steadily, pile up stacks of foraged goods that are great for baking and brewing. Once you're a master forager (100+) you can forage special items in certain zones useful for cultural activities.<BR><BR>All of the tradeskills are applied in the coldain prayer shawls quests which you might start taking up in your 40s or so, even fletching! So have fun working on any and all that appeal to you!
<BR>_________________<BR>Yseulte Nankivel, Veeshan Server</FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=186"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of yseulte"></a>
